descript.abstract: Woolpert Inc was contracted by the US Bureau of Reclamation, US Bureau of Reclamation, Upper Colorado Region, Salt Lake City, UT, to accquire color aerial photography between Embudo, New Mexico and Caballo Dam, New Mexico
descript.purpose: This project of work is for the data and photo acquisiton to enable mapping processing which shall include contour maps, dtms/grids/dems, and orthophotography covering the project area.
descript.supplinf: CONTRACT:R10PC40019 (08-CA-40-8258) CONTRACTOR: Woolpert Inc. TASK ORDER: R10PD40072

theme.themekey: ESRI ArcGIS 9.3 shapefile for approximately 265 river miles and 14 designated features stored as lines perpendicular to the main stem. Attribution includes the river mile or designated feature. The location of River Miles RM0 through RM 26.6 and RM232.6 through RM 265 are based on historic locations documented by USBR and supplied to Woolpert in the file “rivmile.shp” whose metadata cites their origination to have been from 2002 photogrammetry of the river channel. River Mile locations between RM26.6 and RM 232.6 where developed by Woolpert using 2012 aerial photography and LiDAR and were scaled between the fixed features labeled herein and held at their historic mile marker designation.

attracc.attraccr: The final, orthoimagery data produced shall meet or exceed National Map Accuracy Standards (NMAS) for 1"=2000 scale map products. The resulting digital orthoimages will have a 1.5'-foot primary pixel resolution, with accurate X,Y ground coordinates, and RGB scale values from 0 to 255.

qattracc.attracce: Points measured will produce an error less than 10.0 foot RMSE.

dataqual.complete: Imagery was controlled by measuring survey ground control and performing aerotriangulation bundle adjustments on the imagery blocks. The surrvey control included: Point Type: Temporary Control Type: Cloth-Painted Target / Photo ID Horizontal Unit: US Survey Foot Vertical Unit: US Survey Foot Horizontal Datum: NAD 83 Vertical Datum: NAVD 88 (via GEOID03) Ground Control System: New Mexico Central

horizpa.horizpar: The final, orthoimagery data produced shall meet or exceed National Map Accuracy Standards (NMAS) for 1"=2000' scale map products. The resulting digital orthoimages will have a 1.5'-foot primary pixel resolution, with accurate X,Y ground coordinates, and RGB scale values from 0 to 255.

qhorizpa.horizpae: The horizontal accuracy requirement meets the FGDC Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standards, Part 3: National Standard for Spatial Data Accuracy (http://www.fgdc.gov/standards/projects/FGDC-standards-projects/accuracy/part3/index_html).

procstep.procdesc: Woolpert utilized aerial imagery and lidar collected in February of 2012 to digitize the stream bank and apparent centerline of the Rio Grande from Elephant Butte Dam at RM 26.6 to Cochiti Dam at RM232.6. River mile labels and ticks within this project area were then moved to the centerline location and scaled along the centerline while holding mile post locations at 14 features along the reach at their historic, designated mile locations. This approach may yield measured, linear distances between fixed features which are greater or smaller than the designated River Mile posts which were scaled to fit the apparent, 2012 main stem location.
